lead_paragraph: PISCATAWAY, N.J., Dec. 3 — Rutgers was trailing an undefeated team by 5 points, and its leading rebounder and defensive stopper was on the bench with four fouls. It did not look good for the Scarlet Knights — that is, until Epiphanny Prince took over.
